OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F433A1731352265
OL,3,CCompany fined after thousands of fish
OL,4,Ckilled by sewage leaking into streams
OL,6,FThe rising main had already been
OL,7,Fidentified by Wessex Water before the
OL,8,Fincident, as a critical main that
OL,9,Fneeded to be monitored, but this was
OL,10,Fnot put in place until after the
OL,11,Fincident.
OL,13,FWessex Water's rising mains are ageing
OL,14,Fand vulnerable to bursting
OL,16,FThe investigation found that a
OL,17,FSeptember 2018 document the company
OL,18,Fsubmitted to Ofwat showed the number
OL,19,Fof rising main bursts had increased
OL,20,Fmarkedly in recent years, running at
OL,21,Fapproximately 70-80 per year.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/16
